{
  "answer": "**In *Yājñavalkya Smṛti* Chapter 1 (verses Yj_1.4–5), Yājñavalkya lists himself among the twenty sages who are the promulgators (*pranetṛ*) of the Dharmaśāstras:**\n\n> [p-0f4ad0] Manu, Atri, Viṣṇu, Hārīta, **Yājñavalkya**, Uśanas, Aṅgiras,  \n> Yama, Āpastamba, Saṃvarta, Kātyāyana, and Bṛhaspati, // Yj_1.4 //  \n>   \n> [p-95ef53] Parāśara, Vyāsa, Śaṅkha, Likhita, Dakṣa, and Gautama,  \n> Śātātapa, and Vasiṣṭha **are the promulgators of the Dharmaśāstras**. // Yj_1.5 //[^1]\n\nThese two verses together name exactly twenty sages (12 in Yj_1.4 + 8 in Yj_1.5), with Yājñavalkya explicitly included in the first.[^1]: /works/unknown-yajnavalkya-smrti-cb88d6/01/translation/#p-0f4ad0",
